race.comment: SHERIDAN STREET (6) has returned in solid form, producing two good runs without breaking through. Carries the big weight but looks to be hitting her straps now and can deliver the winning blow. BOUDICA WARRIOR (13) showed sharp early speed at Yarra Valley, leading into the straight before fighting on gamely for third. No tougher here and gets in well with the claim. Expect her to take plenty of catching. BRONCO REVOLUTION (14) showed pace to lead at Kyneton before fading late. Draws the inside and with the 3kg claim, he should be in this for a long way. NOCI DI COCCO (17) improved last start when a close second at Albury. McDougall takes over and he commands respect. DENSETSU (5) has been consistent, narrowly missing fresh and following up with a solid Gundagai effort. Peaking now and is right among the chances.
